'''Kunitsuhiko-no-Mikoto Shrine''' (くにつひこのみことじんじゃ) is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} in Hattachi, {{ill|lt=Matsuyama|Q200022|qid=Q200022|1=Matsuyama}} (former {{ill|lt=Hōjō|Q94789|qid=Q94789|1=Hōjō, Ehime}}), {{ill|lt=Ehime Prefecture|Q123376|qid=Q123376|1=Ehime Prefecture}}. Its former rank was {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=kensha|1=Ken-sha|qid=Q90139226}}. It stands atop a {{ill|lt=kofun|Q1141225|qid=Q1141225|1=Kofun}} (Kunitsuhiko-no-Mikoto Shrine Kofun; total length 50 m).

=== Overview ===
The enshrined deity is {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Nigihayahi-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}. He is also called Amaterukuniteruhikoame-no-hoakari-kushitama-nigihayahi-no-Mikoto. Although it is called Kunitsuhiko-no-Mikoto Shrine, the deity is an {{ill|lt=Amatsukami and Kunitsukami|Q11442793|qid=Q11442793|lt=Amatsukami|1=Amatsukami and Kunitsukami}}.

{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Umashimaji-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}, Mononobe no Asari no Mikoto, and {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q317997|lt=Hondawake-no-Mikoto|1=Emperor Ōjin|qid=Q317997}} are also enshrined.

It faces {{ill|lt=Kushitama-hime-no-Mikoto Shrine|Q134888243|qid=Q134888243|1=Kushitamahime Shrine}}. Locally, the two shrines together are called "Kazahaya-no-Miya Ōujigami."
