=== Precinct shrines ===
*Kotohira-gū (deity: {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q10936701|lt=Ōmononushi-no-Kami|1=Ōmononushi}})
*Inari-sha (deity: {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Inari Ōkami|1=UNKNOWN}})
<gallery>
画像:Kunitsuhikonomikoto-jinja 20240912 (4).jpg|Kotohira-gū
画像:Kunitsuhikonomikoto-jinja 20241107 (2).jpg|Inari-sha
</gallery>

=== Annual festival ===
On the first day of the October three-day holiday, the Godōza Festival is held; on the second day, the Shinkō Festival is held.

Called the Kazahaya Fire Festival, it includes throwing a mikoshi down stone steps, and is one of Japan's three major "rough mikoshi" festivals<ref>The other two are Miyagi's "Hote Matsuri" and Himeji's "Nada no Kenka Matsuri".</ref>.

=== Cultural properties ===
*Rōmon gate (Ehime Prefecture designated tangible cultural property)<ref>[https://www.city.matsuyama.ehime.jp/kanko/kankoguide/rekishibunka/bunkazai/ken/kunituhiko_roumon.html Matsuyama City website]</ref>

